<subSubSection id="C320B6A37A584A71FCC0FE86D948FCC6" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" type="description">
<paragraph id="8B85E5287A584A71FCC0FE86DE79FD48" blockId="5.[824,1463,326,1706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">
Pileus 
<quantity id="4CC248CD7A584A71FC8EFE86D9C2FEB9" box="[886,993,326,346]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.15" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="3.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" unit="mm" value="51.5" valueMax="65.0" valueMin="38.0">38–65 mm</quantity>
, hemispherical then plano-convex, glabrous, glutinous, margin yellow (2A4–2A5), towards centre soon becoming more or less brown (6D6–6D7–7D7). Lamellae emarginate, greyish violet (17A2–17A2), most coloured towards the edge. Stipe 40– 
<date id="FF84C3E87A584A71FC24FE01DE19FE36" box="[988,1082,449,469]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" value="1960-10-08" valueMax="1960-10-15" valueMin="1960-10-08">
60 X 
<quantity id="4CC248CD7A584A71FBF4FE01DE4FFE36" box="[1036,1132,449,469]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.15" metricValueMax="1.5" metricValueMin="0.8" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" unit="mm" value="11.5" valueMax="15.0" valueMin="8.0">8–15 mm</quantity>
</date>
, with a marginate bulb (– 
<quantity id="4CC248CD7A584A71FA64FE01D946FE10" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" unit="mm" value="35.0">35 mm</quantity>
), whitish, sometimes with a fugacious violaceous tinge in the upper part. Bulbipellis and mycelium white, bulb margin (veil) stains brown (6D6-6D7). Context whitish. Taste mild and smell neutral to slightly earth-like. Spores narrowly amygdaliform to slightly citriform with narrow apex, with coarse ornament, 9.5–10(–10.5) X 
<quantity id="4CC248CD7A584A71FBACFDB8DEE1FD6F" box="[1108,1218,632,652]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" metricValueMax="6.5" metricValueMin="5.5" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" unit="mm" value="6.0" valueMax="6.5" valueMin="5.5">5.5–6.5 µm</quantity>
, average 10.1 ± 0.3 X 5.7 ± 
<quantity id="4CC248CD7A584A71FC96FD57D997FD48" box="[878,948,663,683]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" unit="mm" value="0.3">0.3 µm</quantity>
; Q ¼ 1.77 ± 0.10.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8B85E5287A584A71FCA0FD75D948FCC6" blockId="5.[824,1463,326,1706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">Chemical reactions: KOH on pileipellis brick-red (9C8) to red brown (9E8) within 60 s, darkest on centre, on bulbipellis pastel red (9A4–9A5), in context negative to very weak rose.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C320B6A37A584A71FCA0FCEFDF85FC63" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" type="biology_ecology">
<paragraph id="8B85E5287A584A71FCA0FCEFDF85FC63" blockId="5.[824,1463,326,1706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">
Habitat: Frondose forests with Fagus sylvatica, Carpinus betulus and Quercus spp. At the 
<typeStatus id="54815B8A7A584A71FB68FC8EDE9EFC81" box="[1168,1213,846,866]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">type</typeStatus>
locality we also found 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FCC0FCACD9E4FC63" authorityName="Reumaux" authorityYear="1993" box="[824,967,876,896]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="nymphicolor">C. nymphicolor</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FC2BFCACDE7EFC63" authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1939" box="[979,1117,876,896]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="arcuatorum">C. arcuatorum</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FB91FCACDEE8FC63" authorityName="Rob. Henry" authorityYear="1939" baseAuthorityName="J. E. Lange" box="[1129,1227,876,896]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="citrinus">C. citrinus</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FB07FCACDF83FC63" box="[1279,1440,876,896]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="xanthophyllus">C. xanthophyllus</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C320B6A37A584A71FCA0FC4BD988F9DC" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B85E5287A584A71FCA0FC4BD988F9DC" blockId="5.[824,1463,326,1706]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">
Observations/Discussion: 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FBABFC4BDEEAFC7C" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[1107,1225,907,927]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="chailluzii">C. chailluzii</taxonomicName>
is recognised by the bright yellow pileus margin, which contrasts the brown centre, recalling the oxidation seen in several fulvoid species, and distinguishing it from 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FBAAFC27DE9BFC18" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[1106,1208,999,1019]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cisticola">C. cisticola</taxonomicName>
, which has a more uniformly coloured pileus. Other similar species have either a negative reaction (C. calochrous, 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FB62FBE4DF45FBDB" authorityName="Moënne-Locc. &amp; Reumaux" authorityYear="2001" box="[1178,1382,1060,1080]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="ochraceopallescens">C. ochraceopallescens</taxonomicName>
etc.) or an intense pink KOH reaction (
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FB8CFB82DED2FBB5" authorityName="Consiglio" authorityYear="1997" box="[1140,1265,1090,1110]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="catharinae">C. catharinae</taxonomicName>
) on the bulbipellis. Microscopically, it occupies an intermediate position (
<figureCitation id="1301F9AD7A584A71FA8FFBA1DF95FB96" box="[1399,1462,1121,1141]" captionStart="Fig 2" captionStartId="3.[138,170,1896,1916]" captionTargetBox="[245,1355,178,1864]" captionTargetId="figure@3.[245,1355,178,1864]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="Fig 2 – Basidiospores. (A) Cortinarius albertii, TF2000-058 (holotype). (B) C. chailluzii, TSJ2000-085 (holotype). (C) C. cisticola, TSJ2002-081 (holotype). (D) C. langeorum, TF2000-012 (holotype). (E) C. sancti-felicis, TSJ2002-072 (holotype) (F) C. selandicus, TF2004-104 (holotype). (G) C. vesterholtii, TT1997-009 (holotype). (H) C. catharinae, TF2004-105. Scale bar = 10 Mm in each case." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366474/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">Figs 2</figureCitation>
and 
<figureCitation id="1301F9AD7A584A71FC91FBBFD9A6FB70" box="[873,901,1151,1171]" captionStart="Fig 3" captionStartId="4.[126,158,1702,1722]" captionTargetBox="[130,759,245,1668]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[128,761,243,1670]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="Fig 3 – Spore scatter diagrams with each point representing average spore size of single collections. (A) Cortinarius albertii and C. catharinae (B) C. calochrous, C. catharinae, C. chailluzii, C. cisticola and C. sublilacinopes. (C) C. vesterholtii, C. insignibulbus, C. nymphicolor, C. parasuaveolens, C. sanctifelicis and C. selandicus." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3366478/files/figure.png" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">3B</figureCitation>
), and with the limited knowledge of its variation it might be difficult to separate from several others on microscopy alone. Presently, we only know this species from two collections including the type. The collection published under the name 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FC5FFB3ADF23FAED" authority="in Consiglio et al. (2004)" authorityName="in Consiglio et al." authorityYear="2004" box="[935,1280,1274,1294]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caroli">
C. caroli in 
<bibRefCitation id="EFAB98D97A584A71FBD8FB3ADF23FAED" author="Consiglio G &amp; Bidaud A &amp; Antonini D &amp; Antonini M &amp; La Rocca S" box="[1056,1280,1274,1294]" journalOrPublisher="Bollettino dell'Associazione Micologica ed Ecologica Romana" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" pagination="3 - 43" part="61" refId="ref13765" refString="Consiglio G, Bidaud A, Antonini D, Antonini M, La Rocca S, 2004. Il Genere Cortinarius in Italia. Parte terza. Alcune specie interessanti della sezione Calochroi. Bollettino dell'Associazione Micologica ed Ecologica Romana 61: 3 - 43." title="Il Genere Cortinarius in Italia. Parte terza. Alcune specie interessanti della sezione Calochroi" type="journal article" year="2004">Consiglio et al. (2004)</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
has an identical ITS sequence and morphology and represents the second record of this species. (For a discussion of the binomial 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FA9FFAF7DF96FAA8" authorityName="in Consiglio et al." authorityYear="2004" box="[1383,1461,1335,1355]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="caroli">C. caroli</taxonomicName>
see the discussion under 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FBC6FA95DE80FA8A" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[1086,1187,1365,1385]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="cisticola">C. cisticola</taxonomicName>
.) The species is named after the forest where we first found it, Forêt du Chailluz, in Doubs, 
<collectingCountry id="F32DA5B87A584A71FC74FA52D9F6FA45" box="[908,981,1426,1446]" name="France" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">France</collectingCountry>
. As we have only encountered the species once ourselves among many hundred collections of calochroid species, it seems probable that the species is very rare in the investigated area. An ITS sequence from the 
<typeStatus id="54815B8A7A584A71FA87FA2ED946F9C2" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">holotype</typeStatus>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3A9EAB7A584A71FC64F9CDDE35F9C2" authorityName="Frøslev &amp; Jeppesen &amp; Laessøe" authorityYear="2006" box="[924,1046,1549,1569]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Cortinariaceae" genus="Cortinarius" kingdom="Fungi" order="Agaricales" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="chailluzii">C. chailluzii</taxonomicName>
is available at GenBank (accession 
<accessionNumber id="946978CB7A584A71FCC0F9EBD9BDF9DC" box="[824,926,1579,1599]" httpUri="http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/nucleotide/DQ323962" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">
<collectionCode id="ED2B7DED7A584A71FCC0F9EBD975F9DC" box="[824,854,1579,1599]" pageId="5" pageNumber="1051">DQ</collectionCode>
323962
</accessionNumber>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
